<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Sim_Whims" s="74178">
  <T n="category">10175<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_SimLife--></T>
  <T n="name">0xFC8D5C59<!--String: "Whims"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Whims_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:75d4e33702edf705</T>
      <T n="text">0x2777FE56<!--String: "Whims are quick to short term goals that your Sims have for themselves.  Whims will appear as thought balloons around your Sim's thumbnail in the lower left."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Whims_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:75d4e33702edf706</T>
      <T n="text">0x16CE1E4A<!--String: "Hover over a Whim to find out more detail about what your Sim wants to do.\n\nThe description will tell you what and how you can accomplish each Whim, as well as the Satisfaction reward, which you can use in the Rewards Store."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Whims_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:75d4e33702edf707</T>
      <T n="text">0xD915BA00<!--String: "The left-most Whim is the Emotional Whim.  The Emotional Whim is always either something about helping your Sim stay in or transition out of their current Emotion."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Whims_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:75d4e33702edf700</T>
      <T n="text">0xB174E7B5<!--String: "You can ignore a Whim, it will not have a negative impact on your Sim.\n\nYou can also dismiss current Whims by clicking on the X next to the Whim thought balloon. This will remove that Whim from your Sim, and eventually refresh with a new Whim after a short period of time."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <T n="ui_sort_order">245</T>
</I>